,"attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4195"},"text":"132 Stat. 4195","children":[],"tail":", 4243; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/60/dG/tLXXII/s7201/j"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–60, div. G, title LXXII, § 7201(j)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-12-18"},"text":"Dec. 18, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/1686"},"text":"139 Stat. 1686","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id567dcd86-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id567dcd87-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section defines in general terms, for the first time in any statute, all the primary duties of the Coast Guard. It is derived from title 14, U.S.C., 1946 ed., §§ 45, 50k–50","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":", 51, 52, 53, 55, 60, 61, 62, 63, 98a, 104, 261, 301, title 33, U.S.C., 1946 ed., §§ 720, 720a, 740, 740a, 740b, title 46, U.S.C., 1946 ed., §§ 1 (footnote), 2 (R.S. 1536, 2747, 2758, 2759, 4249; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1874-06-23/ch455/s1"},"text":"June 23, 1874, ch. 455, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/18/220"},"text":"18 Stat. 220","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1878-06-18/ch265/s4"},"text":"June 18, 1878, ch. 265, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/20/163"},"text":"20 Stat. 163","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1884-07-05/ch221/s2"},"text":"July 5, 1884, ch. 221, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/23/118"},"text":"23 Stat. 118","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1903-02-14/ch552/s10"},"te